ference. The author provides a pragmatic and ultimately hopeful view of the dynamics of diversity in everyday life, offering valuable insights for social policy and practice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh1 aWessendorf, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311129965540uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781529235760?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529235760zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529235760/original  a978-3-11-129965-5 Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA